<subSubSection id="C33DCEFFFFEA0822FF01FE9AFB4BDCD5" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B989D74FFEA0822FF01FE9AFB4BDCD5" blockId="6.[166,1225,367,490]" pageId="6" pageNumber="81">
It should be noted that, despite the considerable length, Siberia and the Far East complex is characterised by the uniformity of the ectoparasite fauna. The only exception — flea 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E6F7FFEA0822FF0FFE45FEEBDCF6" authorityName="Medvedev" authorityYear="1986" box="[213,361,432,457]" class="Insecta" family="Ischnopsyllidae" genus="Ischnopsyllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonaptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis id="B9534166FFEA0822FF0FFE45FEEBDCF6" box="[213,361,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="81">I. ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found only in the Far East. Perhaps the species is more widespread, and the lack of finds in Western and Eastern Siberia is due to insufficient knowledge of the area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
